Prosecuting attorney Samuel Thomas Berg in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Katelyn V Armstrong in court. Right to attorney options form given; referred to State Public Defenders Office. Defendant given complaint; charges/penalties explained by the court. Reading of complaint waived. Minutes filed.
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Signed bond filed with the court.

Defendant shall not possess or consume alcohol. Defendant shall not possess or use illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia. Defendant will not possess any firearms, ammunition or other weapons. Defendant will not in any way contact or attempt to contact any victim(s) listed and will avoid their residence/place of employment or any place they are located and will avoid causing any other person, other than defendant's attorney, from doing so on defendant's behalf.  The term "no contact" is hereby defined as through the mail, by telephone, by way of electronic device, in person, or through a third party.  VICTIM(S)/RESIDENCE(S): NO CONTACT WITH DEPUTY OR SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT, EXCEPT FOR EMERGENCIES. NO CONTACT WITH VEGAS CLUB. Defendant shall personally ensure that payments are made under any Order for Income Withholding if the Court appoints an attorney for the defendant.

Called at 1:41 PM. JJ Crawford for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney Jason Daane appears specially. Record by State. $10000 RoR bond set. Minutes filed.
